channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Base-Metal Demand From Energy Transition to Offset Some China Real-Estate Losses, SMM Says
item.description: Base-metals demand in China will be largely driven by electric vehicles, renewable power, lithium-ion batteries and related infrastructure investment in 2025, offsetting some losses from a weaker property market, the Shanghai Metals Exchange said.

item.title: Stellantis and Aston Martin shares drop sharply after profit warnings amid China woes
item.description: Stocks of European carmakers hemorrhaged early on Monday as Stellantis and British luxury brand Aston Martin issued profit warnings.

item.title: The Surprise Market Winner of 2024: The Great British Pound
item.description: The pound was mocked as the “Great British Peso” not long ago. Suddenly, it is the best-performing currency in developed markets.

item.title: We're upping our price target on Costco after another steady quarter fortifies our thesis
item.description: The retailer's fourth-quarter results were mixed, but we have more conviction in Costco's appeal to shoppers.

item.title: That 5% CD Is a Great Deal---Until the Bank Calls It Back
item.description: With the Fed cutting interest rates, some savers are learning that there is fine print on their certificates of deposit.

item.title: H&M shares fall as much as 8% on profit miss and scrapped earnings margin target
item.description: Shares of H&M tumbled as much as 8% on Thursday after the world's second-largest listed fashion retailer posted a miss on operating profit.

item.title: Euro Stays Weaker Against Dollar After Eurozone Inflation Data
item.description: The euro remained weaker against the dollar after data showed eurozone inflation eased in September as expected.

item.title: Darden Restaurants earnings disappoint as Olive Garden, fine dining sales struggle
item.description: Olive Garden parent Darden Restaurants reported weaker-than-expected earnings and revenue for its fiscal first quarter.

item.title: Oil Falls as Increased Supply Prospects Offset Middle East Fears
item.description: Oil prices edged lower in early European trading as prospects of increased supply from OPEC+ offset risks of supply disruptions in the Middle East.

item.title: We ranked the latest earnings reports from 30 portfolio stocks from great to ugly
item.description: Our companies' performances were reflective of the S&P 500 firms in aggregate.
